bbcode_enabled = true
text = "This code uses an [color=#061E29]if-else[/color] statement to check whether a student passed or failed based on a score.

Purpose of the program:
- Compare the value of [color=#061E29]score[/color] with [color=#061E29]75[/color].
- Display “PASS” if the score is 75 or higher.
- Display “FAIL” if the score is below 75.

[color=#061E29]public class Main[/color]
- Defines the main class of the program.
- The class name is [color=#061E29]Main[/color].

[color=#061E29]public static void main(String[] args)[/color]
- Main method where the program starts running.

[color=#061E29]int score = ___;[/color]
- Declares an integer variable named [color=#061E29]score[/color].
-  Stores the student’s score.

Example:
int score = 80;

[color=#061E29]if (score >= 75)[/color]
- Checks if the score is greater than or equal to 75.
- [color=#061E29]>=[/color] means “greater than or equal to”.

If the condition is true:
System.out.println(\"PASS\");
Displays PASS.

If the condition is false:
System.out.println(\"FAIL\");
Displays FAIL.

Main concept:
1.  [color=#061E29]if[/color] checks a condition.
2. [color=#061E29]else[/color] runs when the condition is false.
3. Used for decision-making in programs.


"

